Build passes. Here's what was changed and why:

**`src/pages/Files.tsx`** — two additions:

1. `handlePageDragEnter` callback (line ~255): detects when external files are dragged over the page (`dataTransfer.types` includes `'Files'`) and auto-reveals the upload zone, so users don't have to click "Upload" first.

2. Wrapped the page content in `<div onDragEnter={handlePageDragEnter}>` so the entire page surface is a drag target.

The UploadZone and folder navigation were already fully implemented — the only genuine UX gap was that dragging files onto a collapsed upload panel did nothing.
